  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The user fires a blast of his blood towards the enemy. If cast as an attack action, the jutsu fires one bullet towards an enemy. This jutsu can be used as a full-attack action to fire as many bullets as the user would normally be able to attack with a full-attack. Each bullet requires a ranged attack roll to hit and deals 2d6 damage. The bullets count as the user's Blood Weapon for all purposes. When a bullet hits the target, you may have it dissipate and reform in your body, returning the Con, but you may not do this if the bullet misses.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Blood Mage (f), Blood Training (a)</p>\n",
